main event: Four brightly illuminated, diamond-shaped objects traveled in formation over Kent, England on 27 October 1955.
interesting points: The objects were accompanied by a radar return., They made no sound., The objects were estimated to be at an altitude of 800 - 1000 feet., A circular object was reported hovering over the aerodrome by an RAF intelligence officer on 16 May 1953., Several civilian crews at sea reported seeing a similar brilliant light moving erratically at approximately the same time.
sighted object: four diamond-shaped objects and a circular hovering object
